Update the data generation process by using the following prompt

Generate a simulated dataset of 200 obligors, with:

100 Corporate Banking obligors and 100 CRE obligors and each data point on a quarterly basis for period between the Origination_date and current date. 

Each obligor can have 1–3 facilities

All facilities for the same obligor must share the same Obligor Name across time, Also same Obligor Rating at any given time period

Each row in the dataset should represent one facility at one timep period and include the following fields. 

Common Fields (for all rows)
Facility ID: unique ID per facility (e.g., F0001, F0002, etc.) No change over time

Obligor Name: e.g., randomly generated company name. No change over time

Obligor Rating: integer between 1 (best) and 16 (worst). Can change over time

Balance: random amount between $1M and $100M. Can change over time

Origination_date: random historical date in last 5 years No change over time

Maturity_date: future date in next 3 years No change over time

LOB: Coporate Banking or CRE No change over time

Corporate Banking-Specific Fields (only for Corporate Banking loans)
Industry: e.g., "Manufacturing", "Retail", "Energy" No change over time

Free Cash Flow: numeric value  Can change over time

Fixed Charge Coverage Ratio: numeric value Can change over time

Cash Flow Leverage: numeric value Can change over time

Liquidity: numeric value Can change over time

Profitability: numeric value Can change over time

Growth: numeric value Can change over time

Leave CRE-specific fields blank or null for these rows.

CRE-Specific Fields (only for CRE loans)
CRE Property Type: e.g., "Office", "Retail", "Multifamily" No change over time

MSA: e.g., "New York", "Dallas", "Chicago" No change over time

NOI (Net Operating Income): numeric value Can change over time

Property Value: numeric value Can change over time

DSCR (Debt Service Coverage Ratio): numeric value Can change over time

LTV (Loan-to-Value): percentage between 0–100% Can change over time

Leave Corporate-specific fields blank or null for these rows.